820 static MCSection *getWinCFISection(MCContext &Context, unsigned *NextWinCFIID, 0
821 MCSection *MainCFISec, ----
822 const MCSection *TextSec) { ----
823 // If this is the main .text section, use the main unwind info section. ----
824 if (TextSec == Context.getObjectFileInfo()->getTextSection()) 0
825 return MainCFISec; 0
826 ----
827 const auto *TextSecCOFF = cast(TextSec); 0
828 auto *MainCFISecCOFF = cast(MainCFISec); 0
829 unsigned UniqueID = TextSecCOFF->getOrAssignWinCFISectionID(NextWinCFIID); 0
830 ----
831 // If this section is COMDAT, this unwind section should be COMDAT associative ----
832 // with its group. ----
833 const MCSymbol *KeySym = nullptr; 0
834 if (TextSecCOFF->getCharacteristics() & COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT) { 0
835 KeySym = TextSecCOFF->getCOMDATSymbol(); 0
836 ----
837 // In a GNU environment, we can't use associative comdats. Instead, do what ----
838 // GCC does, which is to make plain comdat selectany section named like ----
839 // ".[px]data$_Z3foov". ----
840 if (!Context.getAsmInfo()->hasCOFFAssociativeComdats()) { 0
841 std::string SectionName = (MainCFISecCOFF->getName() + "$" + 0
842 TextSecCOFF->getName().split('$').second) 0
843 .str(); 0
844 return Context.getCOFFSection( 0
845 SectionName, ----
846 MainCFISecCOFF->getCharacteristics() | COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT, 0
847 MainCFISecCOFF->getKind(), "", COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ANY); 0
848 } 0
849 } ----
850 ----
851 return Context.getAssociativeCOFFSection(MainCFISecCOFF, KeySym, UniqueID); 0
852 } ----
